  "body": "**üßê Motivation**\r\n\r\nPresently there are gaps declared privately with the identifier `__gap`:\r\n\r\n```ts\r\nuint256[50] private __gap;\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe storage layout output from the Solidity compiler also includes the name of the identifier. I have a simple [tool](https://github.com/zemse/hardhat-storage-layout-changes) that basically allows seeing if the storage layout broke. It basically compares if storage entries with the same identifiers are at the same `slot` and `offset` and it warns/errors if change is spotted. \r\n\r\nCurrently, when a contract inherits a lot of openzeppelin upgradable contracts, there's a bunch of `__gaps` and it's tricky to compare if they were changed. Currently, as a fallback if duplicate identifiers were found, the tool checks if `astId` was changed but `astIds` change easily if there is a considerable solidity code change prior to the variable declaration and then it gets difficult to confirm if the `__gaps` are at the same location.\r\n\r\n**üìù Details**\r\n\r\nI think an easy solution to this problem could be to have unique names for gaps, e.g. including the contract name in it: `__gap_ERC20Upgradeable`.\r\n\r\nOr any suggestions for improving the comparison of storage layout when multiple inherited contracts have private variables with name collision?",
