    "body": "In our own Upgrades Plugin We have implemented an approach to storage layout comparison that works even for gaps that have the same name, so I don't find this a compelling reason to change the name.\r\n\r\nYou should be able to easily reuse our own logic through the `@openzeppelin/upgrades-core` package. This is independent of the plugin, it just consumes Hardhat build info files. See [`getStorageUpgradeReport`](https://docs.openzeppelin.com/upgrades-plugins/1.x/api-core#getstorageupgradereport). Would this work for you?\r\n\r\nIncluding the contract name in the gap could be reasonable but I don't think we should prioritize it, given that we're planning to move away from gaps and instead use the \"diamond storage\" pattern (#2964).",
